channel.title: 1.4 Security Group :: Deploy TensorFlow model on AWS with EC2 and Docker
channel.description: A security group controls the traffic that is allowed to reach and leave the resources that it is associated with. For example, after you associate a security group with an EC2 instance, it controls the inbound and outbound traffic for the instance. Create Security Group At the VPC management console: Click Security groups. Click Create security group. At the Create security group page, enter the following information: Name tag: security-group-inference-1. Description: Allow SSH to developers.
